The MHD Prague takes us on Wednesday for the first time with the chip
On Wednesday, October 1, 2008, the date on which the first passengers enter the subway, tram and bus with an electronic voucher in their pockets instead of a paper ticket is written in the history of the Prague Transport Company.
This can be acquired at the moment by almost a hundred thousand people who own the Opencard chip card.
Passengers can purchase the 30-day, 90-day and annual voucher (this will be valid from 1 January 2009) and simultaneously load it onto their chip card at the infocenters and transport company stalls at Metro stations, Muzeum, Můstek, Nádraží Holešovice, Anděl, Roztyly, Letňany, Kobylisy,
The bonds can be purchased from yesterday on the Internet on the pages of the transport company, www.dpp.cz.
The service, until the afternoon, was used by more than four hundred people.
Those who start using the internet as a form of commerce, can definitely start to forget about ticket stalls at subway stations, where until now they regularly had to queue to get a regular ticket.
