These people portrayed "in the street" are artists capable of transmitting on stage passion, sadness, joy ... captivating the public.
To capture the personality of these artists you do not have to take photos of the stage.
They carry their personality and character inside.
What interested me was to create an intimate atmosphere that would allow me to capture with the camera the personality of the greats of flamenco."
With the flavor of the festival "Cante de las Minas", Bauer began in 1,997 a long journey to portray the singers, guitarists or dancers with a plaque chamber.
They are portraits that, due to the selection of the camera and the material remember the classical photography.
The application of different stylistic media breaks with the classical basis of the image, conferring modernity, an idea that reflects how Bauer himself understands flamenco: "A music with very traditional roots, which evolves and surprises every day".
It is not the action of dance, singing or touching itself, but the personality of the artist, his character, which captivates the public with his art.
The search for an encounter with the essential, with the elf that becomes visible in a way of feeling, being and being are and have been the constant of this work that is presented these days in the gallery The Photographer.
Well-known flamenco figures such as Diego El Cigala, Chano Lobato, Cristina Hoyos, Enrique Morente, El Lebrijano, Antonio Canales, Vicente Amigo, among others, configure this selection of almost seventy artists photographed.
