"We must break the vicious circle of poverty, segregation and unemployment, we must offer Roma children the possibility that guarantees democratic space so that they can contribute to the future of Europe as full citizens," Járóka demanded.
The objective of the European Summit for Equal Opportunities organised annually since last year's Berlin meeting, which was held in the sign of the "European Year of Equal Opportunities", is to ensure a unique forum to promote the abolition of discrimination and equal opportunities at European and national level in the Member States.
Fox in the chicken coop
In the United States, life and health insurance companies, seeing data from the purchase of medication, often deny signing an insurance contract.
Privacy policy specialists fear that the personal data market will become uncontrollable.
"There are programs of protection of personal data, which to the use of the data of the prescriptions in all cases unites it to the approval of the given person.
It must be in independent hands, because if not, "we entrust the chicken coop to the fox" - quotes the Washington Post to Richard Dick, designer of the prescription follow-up program.
Insurance companies make the insurance price and the amount of compensation dependent on the customer’s health status and if they believe the risk is excessive, they simply do not make the contract.
They previously sent the client to medical control and signed the contract with him knowing the result of the control.
Dick ten years ago invented a much cheaper procedure: with the customer identification number he easily gets the list of medicines purchased in the last year and a half and the program itself draws the conclusion about the diseases and health status of the client.
For example, if you systematically take large doses of cholesterol-lowering pills, it indicates that the level of fat in the blood is virtually incurably high, so it is immediately included in a higher risk category.
Numerous versions of the program circulate, some even establish a risk number, so the insurance company in addition to the administration has little to do, although there are small difficulties in this regard.
Among the disadvantages of the program is for example that some medications are multipurpose, for example certain substances serve both to treat headache and heat waves and even antidepressants.
The latter is a major risk increase factor for insurance companies while first-time companies are not.
Special companies were established to consult and process this data, which before acquiring the necessary information from the pharmacies, ask for the approval of the patient.
The authorities already force them to this, although they did not receive a fine for the negligence of so far.
Some companies have also recently developed the results of the laboratory tests and together with the drug consumption data obtain more accurate information about the patient’s health status.
More and more companies have access to this data and simultaneously it is increasingly difficult to control its use.
There is an exclusive law for the protection of personal health data, but it applies only to insurance companies and those providing health services.
The bill that provides the right to the supervisory authority of specialized companies for the provision of personal data is already before Congress.
Dick Richard acknowledges that this is insufficient: he therefore developed his program, which will require the specific approval of the person for the provision of his own personal data.
It is another question that such person cannot deny their approval, because otherwise the insurance companies will not sign with him the contract.
So the chickens, despite everything, are exposed to the goodwill of the fox.
